
[1]rightness

   RIGHTNESS, n.

   1. Correctness; conformity to truth or to the divine will, which is the
   standard of moral rectitude. It is important that a man should have
   such persuasion of the rightness of his conscience as to exclude
   rational doubt.

   2. Straightness; as the rightness of a line.
